node.text: More so than being a recipe book, I want you guys to know how I apply #keto to my life . This isn’t a quick fad. Part 1 of the book is that overall paradigm shift and lifestyle change  that I want you to know. Part 2 will now be the recipes you apply to your new way of life. I can’t wait to see your transformations. Click the LINK IN BIO to preorder . It will be released Sept 24! Thank you !

node.text:
yes this is a dish of pasta on my keto page ... let me explain ... yesterday I wanted a cheat meal ..because I am metabolically flexible .. meaning I’m not always in ketosis and I’ve been doing it so long my body easily switches fuel sources from fat to glucose to fat .. also pasta is yummy... BUT I still prefer to be low carb high fat 90% of the time because it just makes me feel better physically and mentally , I stay lean ,I enjoy delicious fatty satiating meals , and it’s the best food to couple with intermittent fasting IMO.... I like sharing my NON KETO food here as well because my number one pitch for keto is that it gives you the FREEDOM to eat foods like this from time to time . Back in the day when I was 200lbs I was eating this pasta every night ...now I have a foundation of high fat / low carb which Is my way of life .. so sprinkling in some high carb meals is not a bad thing and gives me fun rewards to look forward to ... I’m all about transparency ...That’s why I laugh when people say “bEiNg fUlLy KeTo AlL tHe tImE iS bAd fOr YoU” .. thanks , im not ALWAYS in ketosis. Most people aren’t .. #ketoguido 

PS : carbs meals aren’t always unhealthy .. this dish is healthy-ish with multigrain spaghetti , air fried zucchini , and garlic and oil ... not the best but not cupcakes .

node.text: #KetoGuidoSnackTime Alert! I grew up a cereal head. And even though I no longer eat those sugary morning meals, I still miss that delicious cereal crunch once in a while. The good news is, I don’t have to miss it any more with this delicious treat from @wonderworks_cereal It’s yummy and keto-friendly. So, although I eat it as my treat for the day, it will not throw off my Keto way of life. Also gives me something to eat on the go when I can’t whip up my usual eggs and bacon. Def recommend to get your cereal fix in! #ad #WonderworksCereal #KetoBreakfast

node.text: If you weren’t born with lucky genetics that keep you thin and muscular in this modern world, you’re going to have to follow rules if you want to be lean, toned,and healthy. It’s up to you what you want those rules to be . For example, some diet programs offer You counting low calorie meals so that you are in a caloric deficit but then you can eat whatever food you want in tiny amounts . Some offer pills that speed up your heart rate to burn fat simulating your body exercising . I too follow rules that work for ME. Those are intermittent fasting , eliminating sugars and grains (especially processed), and pretty much eating real food like meat and vegetables ...all  grilled, roasted, or air fried .  With occasional treats ..I also exercise like I’m constantly training for battle.To me these “rules” are the closest to what our ancestors followed. However , theirs were unintentional . They hunted (exercise and acquired meat/fish ), gathered (exercised and acquired leaves , berries, nuts, seeds etc...)and then rested or waited until their next meal was available (intermittent fasting).. i like these rules because I’m never hungry, i eat tasty large meals that I don’t have to count ..and my gut  feels healthy  and how Thousands  of years of evolution intended it to feel. I also naturally fall into a caloric deficit because I’m eating large meals that keep me full, I don’t eat for many hours of the day, and burn crazy calories exercising . I believe my “rules” are the most natural, healthy, realistic , easiest , and sustainable long term..But if people want to try the little calorie meals, pills, cleanses, etc..in this modern world.. to each their own #ketoguido #ketoguidocookbook
